    "department": "Applied AI",
    "description": "ABOUT THE TEAM (INCUBATION)\n\nThe Incubation team builds new product lines from zero to one — exploring bold ideas and turning the most promising ones into real, shipped experiences. We work at the intersection of design, engineering, and research to prototype quickly, learn from real users, and scale what works. Our goal is to unlock entirely new ways people can create, communicate, and get things done with OpenAI’s technology — with a high bar for quality, safety, and craft.\n\n\nABOUT THE ROLE\n\nWe’re looking for an engineer to lead the development of new iOS experiences inside our Incubation team. You’ll help invent and ship early-stage products that bring AI into people’s lives in ways that feel intuitive, human, and genuinely useful. This is a hands-on, high-ownership role: you’ll move fast from prototype to product, help shape product direction through iteration, and lay strong technical foundations as ideas mature into scalable systems.\n\nWe’re looking for engineers who thrive in small, nimble teams, bring strong product instincts, and pair sharp judgment with excellent execution. You should be comfortable operating with ambiguity, running experiments, learning quickly from results, and translating those learnings into both product and architecture decisions.\n\n\nIN THIS ROLE, YOU WILL:\n\n - Build and ship new iOS experiences that demonstrate what’s possible when AI is deeply integrated into the product — from early prototypes to public launches.\n\n - Drive end-to-end development of core features and workflows, using Swift and modern iOS frameworks (SwiftUI/UIKit), with a strong emphasis on craft and UX polish.\n\n - Partner closely with product, design, research, and backend to translate early concepts into delightful, high-leverage user experiences.\n\n - Own performance, reliability, and quality — ensuring the app feels fast, stable, and responsive across devices and geographies.\n\n - Establish strong technical foundations (architecture, testing, observability) that let us iterate quickly now and scale confidently later.\n\n - Contribute technical leadership by raising the bar on iOS engineering practices and helping shape the direction of OpenAI’s mobile platform.\n\n\nYOU MIGHT THRIVE IN THIS ROLE IF YOU:\n\n - Have 5+ years of professional software engineering experience, with a focus on building and scaling iOS applications.\n\n - Have shipped high-quality, user-facing mobile products that balance delightful design with reliability, performance, and resilience.\n\n - Have owned complex mobile systems end-to-end — from architecture and implementation to monitoring, iteration, and improvement.\n\n - Are fluent in Swift and deeply familiar with the Apple ecosystem (Xcode, UIKit, SwiftUI, modern concurrency).\n\n - Make thoughtful architectural tradeoffs that optimize for speed of iteration now and maintainability later.\n\n - Care deeply about creating experiences that feel simple, human, and trustworthy — especially when AI is involved.\n\n - Enjoy building in an environment where product direction is discovered through shipping and learning, not fully specified upfront.\n\nAbout OpenAI\n\nOpenAI is an AI research and deployment company dedicated to ensuring that general-purpose artificial intelligence benefits all of humanity. We push the boundaries of the capabilities of AI systems and seek to safely deploy them to the world through our products. AI is an extremely powerful tool that must be created with safety and human needs at its core, and to achieve our mission, we must encompass and value the many different perspectives, voices, and experiences that form the full spectrum of humanity. \n\nWe are an equal opportunity employer, and we do not discriminate on the basis of race, religion, color, national origin, sex, sexual orientation, age, veteran status, disability, genetic information, or other applicable legally protected characteristic.\n\nFor additional information, please see OpenAI’s Affirmative Action and Equal Employment Opportunity Policy Statement https://cdn.openai.com/policies/eeo-policy-statement.pdf.\n\nBackground checks for applicants will be administered in accordance with applicable law, and qualified applicants with arrest or conviction records will be considered for employment consistent with those laws, including the San Francisco Fair Chance Ordinance, the Los Angeles County Fair Chance Ordinance for Employers, and the California Fair Chance Act, for US-based candidates. For unincorporated Los Angeles County workers: we reasonably believe that criminal history may have a direct, adverse and negative relationship with the following job duties, potentially resulting in the withdrawal of a conditional offer of employment: protect computer hardware entrusted to you from theft, loss or damage; return all computer hardware in your possession (including the data contained therein) upon termination of employment or end of assignment; and maintain the confidentiality of proprietary, confidential, and non-public information. In addition, job duties require access to secure and protected information technology systems and related data security obligations.\n\nTo notify OpenAI that you believe this job posting is non-compliant, please submit a report through this form https://form.asana.com/?d=57018692298241\u0026k=5MqR40fZd7jlxVUh5J-UeA. No response will be provided to inquiries unrelated to job posting compliance.\n\nWe are committed to providing reasonable accommodations to applicants with disabilities, and requests can be made via this link https://form.asana.com/?k=bQ7w9h3iexRlicUdWRiwvg\u0026d=57018692298241.\n\nOpenAI Global Applicant Privacy Policy https://cdn.openai.com/policies/global-employee-and-contractor-privacy-policy.pdf\n\nAt OpenAI, we believe artificial intelligence has the potential to help people solve immense global challenges, and we want the upside of AI to be widely shared. Join us in shaping the future of technology.",
